=== rc.xml ===
{{Path|rc.xml}} is used to specify keybindings and mousebindings. It is located in {{Path|/etc/xdg/openbox}} or {{Path|~/.config/openbox}}.

The following are the modifiers.
{| class="wikitable sortable"
|-
! Key !! Description
|-
| S || Shift key
|-
| C || Control key
|-
| A || Alt key
|-
| W || Super (windows) key
|-
| M || Meta key
|-
| H || Hyper key
|}

To make a keybinding, you can combine modifiers and a key. They are separated with the '-' sign.
{{Important| Case matters. 'S' (uppercase) is the shift key while 's' (lowercase) is the s alphabet key.}}

==== Examples ====
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Keybinding !! Modifier
|-
| Alt-o || A-o
|-
| Ctrl-Alt-x || C-A-x
|-
| Ctrl-Alt-Shift-y || C-A-S-y
|-
| Shift-s || S-s
|}

{{Important| The keybinding should go between ''<keyboard>'' and ''</keyboard>'' in {{Path|rc.xml}}.}}

If you want to open xterm with '''Super-t''', you should add the following to the {{Path|rc.xml}}:
{{File|~/.config/openbox/rc.xml||<pre>
<keybind key="W-t">
  <action name="Execute">
    <command>xterm</command>
  </action>
</keybind>
</pre>}}

You can also bind menus. For example, you can bind openbox right click and middle click menu with the following:
{{File|~/.config/openbox/rc.xml||<pre>
<keybind key="W-x">
  <action name="ShowMenu">
    <menu>root-menu</menu>
  </action>
</keybind>

<keybind key="W-z">
  <action name="ShowMenu">
    <menu>client-list-combined-menu</menu>
  </action>
</keybind>
</pre>}}

In the above example, the right click menu is bound with Super-x, and the middle click menu is bound with Super-z. It is useful especially if you prefer not to use any panel with openbox.

